name: Scallops with Creamy Bacon Sorn Sauce

steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Remove the husks and silk from the ears of corn
- Slice the kernels off the cob (about 2 to 3 cups)
- Coarsely chop the chives


### Steps
1. Preheat a large saute pan on medium high for 2 to 3 minutes
2. Season scallops with salt and pepper
3. Place oil in pan
4. Add scallops to pan
5. Cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes
6. Take scallops out of pan
7. Cut bacon into small pieces and cook for 3 to 4 minutes
8. Drain all but 1 tablespoon of bacon fat
9. Stir in the trinity mix
10. Cook for 2 to 3 minutes, or until soft
11. Combine the blackening seasoning, half & half and corn, ad the mixture to the pan
12. Reduce to medium low
13. Cook for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring frequently
14.Put into bowl, top with scallops and chives
